ich were gold, while South Korea came in second with 10 golds among its 32 medals.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999704579361604, \"rank\": 2.811443337504579e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1413, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999998181011, \"rank\": 1.7322298358602409e-10, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Cheong told The Straits Times that although preparation for the competition was rigorous, and at times she felt lonely training solo, she knew she had to keep herself in good spirits to do well.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Straits Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just needed to shift my mindset to a positive one, and I would be able to do better,\\\" she said, adding that the win came as a surprise to her.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Victoria Cheong beat 13 others from around the world to win a gold medal in the visual merchandising category.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\", \"score\": 0.9998651549023806, \"rank\": 6.503113852362135e-05, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], 